question.text:
Write the class `EvenTest` which tests the implementation of the class `Even` shown below. This class just contains one method `isTrue` which is supposed to return `true` if the passed integer value is an even number. 

```java
class Even {
	public boolean isTrue(int num) {
		if (num % 2 == 0) {
			return true;
		} else {
			return false;
		}
	}
}
```

answer:
import org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;

import static org.junit.jupiter.api.Assertions.*;

public class EvenTest {

    @Test
    public void testEven() {
        assertTrue(new Even().isTrue(1));
    }


}
